-> What Was Used to Build This : 

React (with Vite + TypeScript) — fast and modern
Tailwind CSS — flexible styling system
Framer Motion — smooth animations
Google Fonts — DM Serif Display + Inter to match design exactly
Optimized for desktop layout, because the given Figma design was desktop-only.


Q. Features
Very close visual match to the Figma reference
Gradient borders, shadows, and precise typography
No page scrolling — quiz always fits inside the frame
Animated question transitions (slide + fade)
Hover + selected styling on answers
Dynamic progress bar that increases only once a question is answered
Animated final score
Cute paw badge saying “Best of Luck!”


Q.  Setup & Instructions
Follow these steps to run the project locally:
->Clone or Download the Project
->git clone <YOUR_REPO_LINK>
->cd quiz-assignment
️ 

Q . Install Dependencies
npm install
Run the App in Development Mode
npm run dev

️Q.  Open in Browser
http://localhost:5173


Q.  Assumptions Made
All questions are locally stored — no backend or API
Desktop-focused design (no mobile responsiveness required)
Linear quiz flow with Next / Previous buttons
Score calculation: (correct answers ÷ total questions) × 100

